cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.SE 

This paper is about developing a framework for quantitative analysis of concept drift in machine learning models. It is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it deals with the development of efficient and effective mechanisms to address learning in the context of non-stationary distributions, which is a common problem in these sub-fields.
